⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Phantoon
node MET · MET · ⟦Phantoon:MET:f79488⟧

WHO   — Phantoon — the phantom
WHAT  — The ghostly boss of the Wrecked Ship in Super Metroid — a giant floating phantom that fades from sight, opens its single great eye, and rains down blue flames upon the hunter who dares its dead halls.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Metroid (1986) & Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because it is the thing that killed the ship — a power-draining presence squatting in the wreck, guarding the dark with fire, refusing to let the silence be disturbed by the living.
HOW   — By phasing out of visibility so weapons pass through nothing, by opening its lone eye only to be struck, and by loosing showers of blue flame across the listing chamber until the hunter answers it shot for shot.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the dark that drank the ship — strike my eye, or strike nothing at all.

